cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY

This paper discusses a new mapping technique for bibliometric analysis and compares it with the well-known technique of multidimensional scaling. The paper focuses on constructing maps of authors, journals, and keywords, which are commonly used in the field of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it deals with bibliometric analysis. Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves mapping of keywords, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as they deal with network analysis, and cs.CY (Computational Geometry) as it involves mathematical analysis of the techniques.
